Class AbstractHibernateRepository<T,V extends java.io.Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ncl.botnetwork.AbstractHibernateRepository<T,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.springframework.data.repository.CrudRepository<T,V>, org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<T,V>, org.springframework.data.repository.Repository<T,V>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BNTweetRepository, ConfigRepository, ConnectionRepository, UserRepository

    public class AbstractHibernateRepository<T,V extends java.io.Serializable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.springframework.data.repository.PagingAndSortingRepository<T,V>
    The abstract implementation of the hibernate repository which all other repositories (in this scope) extend. Provides basic, generic operations on the underlying database such as; find, save, and delete.
    Author:
    Jonathan Carlton
    See Also:
